Both reproductions are still running; that is expected for the nested world/project loops. Meanwhile, the first review wave is checking the design’s written contract against those executable semantics, especially the distinction between ratio-of-aggregates, mean per-world `Δ_O`, and the practical-equivalence decision rule.
 succeeded in 79881ms:
SYMMETRY GATE — selection-only, delivery at parity (f=1.0). 100 worlds, seedBase=20260710.
Both arms: same pool/costs/budget/noise; own noisy eligibility (no oracle gate). Central: value-reader + bounded credit (lambda), even appraisal bandwidth.

