audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design\critique-v2-multiplier-estimand.md:58:### 4. Major — `Δ_O` itself has no zero-reference policy
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design\critique-v2-multiplier-estimand.md:64:### 5. Major — “secondary” is a prose promise, not an enforceable output contract
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design\critique-v2-multiplier-estimand.md:76:## Minimum acceptance test for this dimension
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design\critique-v2-dependence-sensitivity.md:3:## Verdict
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design\critique-v2-dependence-sensitivity.md:9:## Specific issues
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design\critique-v2-dependence-sensitivity.md:11:### 1. The proposed dependence restriction is both incomplete and directionally wrong
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design\critique-v2-dependence-sensitivity.md:21:### 2. The joint choice can determine the headline even with identical marginals
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design\critique-v2-dependence-sensitivity.md:23:The shipped E4-v4 special case gives the exact parity law `beta = 1-gamma` (`scripts/simulation/e4-v4-symmetric-frontier.mjs:82-85`). Let `U` be uniform on `[0,1]`, set `gamma=U`, and keep `beta` marginally uniform under each of these copulas:
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design\critique-v2-dependence-sensitivity.md:29:Thus, with the **same uniform marginal for each parameter**, `epsilon=.01` yields a 99% distributed-win mass under one dependence structure, 1% under another, and 100% parity under the limiting countermonotone structure. I independently checked these values over 1,000,000 equally spaced `U` draws. Independent uniforms would yield 50%. The copula alone can therefore choose the region-mass headline.
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design\critique-v2-dependence-sensitivity.md:31:This does not move the mathematical frontier. It determines which parts of the frontier are admissible and how much probability sits on each side. That is why the foundation's proposed headline about “how large each region is” (`research/e4-value-estimation-foundation.md:58-63`) is not identified until a joint measure is defended. Under a mere admissible set, “large” can mean geometric volume only after choosing a coordinate system and base measure; it is not a real-world prevalence.
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design\critique-v2-dependence-sensitivity.md:35:### 3. “Joint distribution / admissible set” presents non-interchangeable alternatives
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design\critique-v2-dependence-sensitivity.md:46:Without this separation, the analyst can obtain a preferred result by choosing a copula, a base measure on the admissible set, or a mixture weight across model forms.
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design\critique-v2-dependence-sensitivity.md:48:### 4. Dependence-aware Shapley is valid only after several missing choices are frozen
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design\critique-v2-dependence-sensitivity.md:60:### 5. Inner-versus-outer separation is stated but not operationalized
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design\critique-v2-dependence-sensitivity.md:70:### 6. “Before running” is not an adequate outcome-blind safeguard here
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design\critique-v2-dependence-sensitivity.md:74:All work to date should be labeled exploratory. A confirmatory preregistration needs an auditable source-to-support file frozen before the replacement engine's outputs are exposed, preferably set or reviewed by someone insulated from those outputs. Admissibility constraints must refer only to institutional/data-generating facts, never to `Delta_O`, parity distance, or which arm wins. Freeze all candidate dependence structures and report every one; do not select the structure with the most stable or attractive Shapley ranking after the run. A held-out seed is useful for code validation but cannot repair post-outcome choice of supports or copulas.
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design\critique-v2-dependence-sensitivity.md:76:## Required fixes before preregistration
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design\critique-v2-dependence-sensitivity.md:80:3. **Preregister dependence as mathematics, not adjectives.** For every candidate law/set, publish marginals, copula or structural equations, deterministic constraints, support, provenance, transport mapping, scenario weights, and conditional-sampling code. Include both favorable and adverse empirically defensible dependence structures.
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design\critique-v2-dependence-sensitivity.md:86:The single sharpest improvement is to make the **conditional frontier invariant and primary**, then place externally justified admissible sets and law-specific probability mass on top of it as visibly secondary layers. That prevents a convenient copula from becoming the result.
